den}}</ref>\n| [https://www.arun.gov.uk/arun-district-councillors URL]\n|-\n| scope=row | [[Ashfield District Council]]\n| Leader of the Council\n| style=\"background-color: {{Independent politician/meta/color}}\" |\n| Jason Zadrozny\n| 26 April 2018<ref>{{cite web|url = https://www.chad.co.uk/news/ashfield-council-leader-toppled-after-dramatic-vote-1-9137584|work = Chad |title = Ashfield council leader toppled after dramatic vote|date = 26 April 2018|first = Jessica|last = Dallison}}</ref>\n| [https://democracy.ashfield-dc.gov.uk/mgCommitteeDetails.aspx?ID=133 URL]\n|-\n| scope=row | [[Ashford Borough Council]]\n|Leader of the Council\n| style=\"background-color: {{Conservative Party (UK)/meta/color}}\" |\n| Gerry Clarkson\n| 18 April 2013<ref>{{cite web|url = http://www.kentonline.co.uk/ashford/news/cllr-gerry-clarkson-new-leader-o-a53701/|title = Cllr Gerry Clarkson new leader of Ashford Borough Council|work = Kent Online|date = 19 April 2013|first = Robert|last = Barman}}</ref>\n| [https://www.ashford.gov.uk/councillors-meetings-and-elections/councillors-and-meetings/how-committees-operate/the-cabinet/ URL]\n|-\n| scope=row | [[Babergh District Council]]\n| Leader of the Council\n| style=\"background-color: {{Conservative Party (UK)/meta/color}}\" |\n| John Ward\n| 4 January 2018<ref>{{cite web|url = https://www.babergh.gov.uk/news/babergh-elects-new-leader/|title =Babergh Elects New Leader|work = Babergh Mid Suffolk|date = 4 January 2018}}</ref>\n| [https://baberghmidsuffolk.moderngov.co.uk/mgCommitteeDetails.aspx?ID=521 URL]\n|-\n| scope=row | [[Barrow-in-Furness Borough Council]]\n| Leader of the Council\n| style=\"background-color: {{Labour Party (UK)/meta/color}}\" |\n| Dave Pidduck\n| May 2011<ref>{{cite web|archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20121008184028/http://www.nwemail.co.uk/news/election-success-as-labour-take-control-1.835292?referrerPath=raiders|url = http://www.nwemail.co.uk/news/election-success-as-labour-take-control-1.835292?referrerPat