s'', 23 August 2017. Retrieved 2 January 2018.</ref> \n|-\n| style=\"background:{{Scottish Labour Party/meta/color}}\" | \n|-\n! scope=row | [[Aberdeenshire Council]]\n| Leader of the council\n| style=\"background:{{Scottish Conservative Party/meta/color}}\" |\n| Jim Gifford\n| May 2012\n| <ref name=COSLA>[http://www.cosla.gov.uk/councils/leaders Council Leaders], Convention of Scottish Local Authorities. Retrieved 2 January 2018.</ref>\n|-\n! scope=row | [[Angus Council]]\n| Leader of the council\n| style=\"background:{{Independent politician/meta/color}}\" |\n| Bob Myles\n| May 2017\n| <ref name=COSLA />\n|-\n! scope=row | [[Argyll and Bute Council]]\n| Leader of the council\n| style=\"background:{{Liberal Democrats/meta/color}}\" |\n| Aileen Morton\n| May 2017\n| <ref name=COSLA />\n|-\n! scope=row | [[Edinburgh City Council]]\n| Leader of the council\n| style=\"background:{{Scottish National Party/meta/color}}\" |\n| Adam McVey\n| May 2017\n| <ref name=COSLA />\n|-\n! scope=row | [[Clackmannanshire Council]]\n| Leader of the council\n| style=\"background:{{Scottish National Party/meta/color}}\" |\n| Les Sharp\n| 3 November 2014\n| <ref>[http://www.alloaadvertiser.com/news/13535979.Les_Sharp_elected_as_new_leader_of_the_council/ \"Les Sharp elected as new leader of the council\"], ''Alloa & Hillfoots Advertiser'', 30 October 2014. Retrieved 2 January 2018.</ref>\n|-\n! scope=row | [[Dumfries and Galloway Council]]\n| Leader of the council\n| style=\"background:{{Scottish Labour Party/meta/color}}\" |\n| [[Elaine Murray]]\n| May 2017\n| <ref name=COSLA />\n|-\n! scope=row | [[Dundee City Council]]\n| Leader of the council\n| style=\"background:{{Scottish National Party/meta/color}}\" |\n| John Alexander\n| May 2017\n| <ref name=COSLA />\n|-\n! scope=row | [[East Ayrshire Council]]\n| Leader of the council\n| style=\"background:{{Scottish National Party/meta/color}}\" |\n| Douglas Reid\n| May 2007\n| <ref>[http://www.heraldscotland.com/news/12745820.Tory_becomes_pr