], [[Wales]] and [[Northern Ireland]]. Council leaders are often representatives of the majority party, or largest party on the council, but can sometimes be representatives of minority administrations or coalition parties.\n\n== England ==\n\n=== Non-metropolitan counties ===\n{{updated|15 March 2018}}\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable plainrowheaders\"\n|-\n! Council\n! Title\n! colspan=2 | Name\n! Since\n! <abbr title=\"Reference\">Ref.</abbr>\n\n|-\n! scope=row | [[Cambridgeshire County Council]]\n| Leader of the Council\n| bgcolor=\"{{Conservative Party (UK)/meta/color}}\" | \n| Steve Count\n| 13 May 2014\n| [https://www.cambridgeshire.gov.uk/council/councillors-&-meetings/county-councillors/committee-membership/ URL]\n|-\n! scope=row | [[Cumbria County Council]]\n| Leader of the Council\n| bgcolor=\"{{Labour Party (UK)/meta/color}}\" | \n| Stewart Young\n| 16 May 2013\n| [http://councilportal.cumbria.gov.uk/mgExecPostDetails.aspx?ID=973 URL]\n|-\n! scope=row | [[Derbyshire County Council]]\n| Leader of the Council\n| bgcolor=\"{{Conservative Party (UK)/meta/color}}\" | \n| Barry Lewis\n| 24 May 2017\n| [https://www.derbyshire.gov.uk/council/council_works/cabinet/cabinet_members/default.asp URL]\n|-\n! scope=row | [[Devon County Council]]\n| Leader of the Council\n| bgcolor=\"{{Conservative Party (UK)/meta/color}}\" | \n| John Hart\n| 25 June 2009\n| [http://democracy.devon.gov.uk/mgExecPostDetails.aspx?ID=143 URL]\n|-\n! scope=row | [[Dorset County Council]]\n| Leader of the Council\n| bgcolor=\"{{Conservative Party (UK)/meta/color}}\" |\n| Rebecca Knox\n| 18 May 2017\n| [http://dorset.moderngov.co.uk/mgExecPostDetails.aspx?ID=241 URL]\n|-\n! scope=row | [[East Sussex County Council]]\n| Leader of the Council\n| bgcolor=\"{{Conservative Party (UK)/meta/color}}\" |\n| Keith Glazier\n| 21 May 2013\n| [https://democracy.eastsussex.gov.uk/mgExecPostDetails.aspx?ID=175 URL]\n|-\n! scope=row | [[Essex County Council]]\n| Leader of the Council\n| bgcolor=\"{{Conservativ