tish Labour Party/meta/color}}\" |\n| Jim Logue\n| 8 March 2016\n| <ref>[http://www.heraldscotland.com/news/homenews/14310230.Scots_council_has_new_leader_for_the_first_time_in_almost_two_decades/ \"Scots council has new leader for the first time in almost two decades\"], ''The Herald'' (Glasgow), 29 February 2016. Retrieved 2 January 2018.</ref>\n|-\n! scope=row | [[Orkney Islands Council]]\n| Leader of the council\n| style=\"background:{{Independent politician/meta/color}}\" |\n| James Stockan\n| May 2017\n| <ref name=COSLA />\n|-\n! scope=row | [[Perth and Kinross Council]]\n| Leader of the council\n| style=\"background:{{Scottish Conservative Party/meta/color}}\" |\n| Ian Campbell\n| May 2017\n| <ref name=COSLA />\n|-\n! scope=row | [[Renfrewshire Council]]\n| Leader of the council\n| style=\"background:{{Scottish National Party/meta/color}}\" |\n| Iain Nicolson\n| May 2017\n| <ref name=COSLA />\n|-\n! scope=row | [[Scottish Borders Council]]\n| Leader of the council\n| style=\"background:{{Scottish Conservative Party/meta/color}}\" |\n| Shona Haslam\n| May 2003\n| <ref name=COSLA />\n|-\n! scope=row | [[Shetland Islands Council]]\n| Leader of the council\n| style=\"background:{{Independent politician/meta/color}}\" |\n| Cecil Smith\n| May 2017\n| <ref name=COSLA />\n|-\n! scope=row | [[South Ayrshire Council]]\n| Leader of the council\n| style=\"background:{{Scottish National Party/meta/color}}\" |\n| Douglas Campbell\n| May 2007\n| <ref name=COSLA />\n|-\n! scope=row | [[South Lanarkshire Council]]\n| Leader of the council\n| style=\"background:{{Scottish National Party/meta/color}}\" |\n| John Ross\n| May 2017\n| <ref name=COSLA />\n|-\n! scope=row | [[Stirling Council]]\n| Leader of the council\n| style=\"background:{{Scottish National Party/meta/color}}\" |\n| Scott Farmer \n| May 2012\n| <ref name=COSLA />\n|-\n! scope=row | [[West Dunbartonshire Council]]\n| Leader of the council\n| style=\"background:{{Scottish National Party/meta/color}}\" |\n| Jonathan